HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 427
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Emma Boshers, 2025
Top Ten Senior of Mt. Pleasant High School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Emma Boshers is one such exceptional student, who was recently named a
Top Ten Senior of the 2025 graduating class at Mt. Pleasant High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. Boshers has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Emma Boshers has earned an
exemplary grade point average of 98.07 while participating in numerous extracurricular
activities, including FFA, student council, and Beta Club; and
WHEREAS, following her graduation, Ms. Boshers plans to study animal science, a field
that she has an abiding passion for, and then attend Middle Tennessee State University and
earn a master's degree in the same, with which she aims to enter veterinary school to earn a
subsequent degree in veterinary science; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Boshers's display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well
for her future success; and
WHEREAS, her noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of pride for her family,
her school, and her community; and
